-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 17
-- 
-- Fri Oct 17, 2014 02:03AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 17 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Centre-right GERB party reached an agreement with nationalist Patriotic Front to form a government. The two parties lack parliamentary majority and a third party is needed for a government. (Trud, Standart, Sega, Capital Daily, 24 Chasa) TRUD - The interim government is ready to present its proposal for 2015 budget by the end of the month, if the political parties fail to form a government by then, sources familiar with the plans said. The budget needs a parliament approval.  - The central bank said that the Austrian consultancy EPIC has not presented necessary documents to prove its represents all shareholders in troubled Corporate Commercial Bank <6C9.BB> and has not shown their commitment to provide financial support. (Standart, Presa, Sega, Capital Daily)